events.description:

events.name: Android Study Jams
events.description:
This is a supporting study jam group for the online training course UD837 from Udacity.

Please register with Udacity using this link here: Study Jams registration @Udacity

At the course page, make sure to use the option "Preview Course" or "Access free materials" for using the cost-free path.

Start going through the lessons, and we will review the content afterwards using the following time schedule:

• 20 April: Lessons 1A + 1B (including Practice Set 1)

• 22 April: Lessons 2A + 2B (including Practice Set 2)

• 27 April: Lessons 3A + 3B

• 29 April: Final Project

Most won't be able to finish the final project, so you will be able to share that afterwards online as well.

events.name: Red Hat and Google Technology Tour
events.description:
This is not an event by us but organized by Red Hat and Google.

Google brings its experience to run apps at scale and their public cloud offerings. Red Hat has the experience and standing in Enterprise IT. In this event we combine both and talk about OpenShift Enterprise which  is the container based application development and production environment by Red Hat with Kubernetes at its core. OpenShift gives you the flexibility to address your on premise and public cloud needs and allows you to make hybrid cloud scenarios real.

The talks will be in German.

Participation is free, but you have to register here:

https://www.redhat.com/de/about/events/google-tour-2016-wien

events.name: Google I/O wrap-up & Google Cloud Platform
events.description:

And Robert Kubis, Developer Advocate at Google, is giving a talk on latest development around the Google Cloud Platform.

events.name: droidcon Vienna
events.description:
droidcon comes to Vienna this year!

From 16 to 17 September at Technikum Wien, droidcon Vienna will feature more than 20 sessions in three parallel tracks, with over fifteen hours of high-quality content.

The speaker lineup is already impressive, content will include Firebase, Kotlin, Android Auto and more.

Ticket purchase is needed - head over to droidcon.at for all details and the registration.

As a GDG Vienna member you get 20% discount of the regular price. Please use the discount code gdg-vienna at checkout!

events.name: #WTMVIE organises a Workshop: Overcoming Impostor Syndrome
events.description:
Do you feel like a fraud? Are you not sure whether you can do the work you are supposed to?

You are not alone, and many high-achievers are unable to internalize and accept their successes. They often attribute their accomplishments to luck rather than to ability, and fear that others will eventually unmask them as a fraud.

This workshop will help you identify and deal with the impostor syndrome. You will make the first steps in overcoming your fears and foster your confidence in your abilities.

events.description:

• Your talk! (ideally Google Assistant related, but can be other Google-stuff, how-long-you want)

• GDG Vienna Plans & Announcements (5 minutes)

• Beer, drinks, snacks & networking

Again Google will sponsor drinks & snack for us - thank you Google!

events.name: Vienna Kaggle: Deep Learning with Tensorflow on the Google Cloud
events.description:
This is a joint meetup with Vienna Kaggle!

As you might know, Kaggle has been acquired by Google.

So it is only natural to celebrate this and have a joint Meetup with Vienna Kaggle @Stockwerk!

In this interactive Meetup we will do a hands-on-session to enable machine learning in the cloud and make a submission to the starter kaggle competition Digit Recognizer, so bring your laptops!

This is a good chance to get your feet wet with Kaggle, Deep Learning, Tensorflow and the Google Cloud.

The Agenda:

• google cloud account setup (comes with 300 bucks of play credits), trial: https://console.cloud.google.com/freetrial

• create kaggle account, link: https://www.kaggle.com/?login=true

• setup a cloud project with tensorflow 

• enable machine learning apis 

• train/validate/test model 

• make a submission 

• train/validate/test model, make a submission, ....

Looking forward meeting you,

  Helmuth, Christoph and László

Looking forward to meeting you soon!

events.name: Vienna Kaggle Coding Session @ Google
events.description:
This will be again a joint meetup with our friends from Vienna Kaggle - first time in the Google office.

Special thanks to Christoph from Vienna Kaggle and Beate from Google to make this happen!

We will work on the Carvana Image Masking competition, an image segmentation challenge - which is perfect to play aroud with U-Net and other Deep Learning architectures.

--- 

This is a hands-on session, so please make sure you bring your laptop and all your questions about the competition, data mining and machine learning to the Coding Session!

---

I strongly recommend you to sign up for a free Google Cloud account (requires a credit card) beforehand, which gives you 300$ credits for playing around with GPUs and other cool stuff on Google Cloud.

We will offer ready-to-run Jupyter notebooks for this competition to get you started smoothly. Hence, if you create your Google Cloud account now you wont have any troubles getting started during the competition.

Looking forward to working with you on this challenge!

events.name: Flutter Introduction & Codelab
events.description:
Let's talk about Flutter!

Flutter is a new way of writing mobile apps for Android and iOS using a unified codebase.

We will start with an introduction of Flutter, and then go through the codelab together for your first mobile app in Flutter.

Agenda

• What is Flutter - Introduction

• Comparison to alternatives (native / hybrid / React Native / NativeScript)

• Showcase - a look into a (not so small) Flutter application

• Codelab - your first steps into developing Flutter applications

For the best experience with the Codelab please bring your laptop with you!

If you want to have a head start you might want to pre-install the Flutter SDK prior to the meetup: flutter.io/setup/

events.name: Meet the team: Firebase
events.description:
Directly from the Firebase summit in Prague we will be welcoming Diana & Kiana from the Firebase team.

Diana is a Software Engineer from the Firebase team. She is continuously adding more awesome features, specially for Firebase Hosting and Cloud Functions for Firebase.

Kiana McNellis is a Developer Programs Engineer on Firebase. Her focus is on improving the developer experience by coordinating the developer support program.

They will give a short presentation on Firestore, following some discussion on best practices.

In addition we will have a Firebase Codelab for Android - if that's for you then bring your Laptop PC w/ Android Studio installed!

events.name: DACHFest 2018 (DevFest DACH)
events.description:
For this year's DevFest season, GDG and WTM communities of Germany, Austria, and Switzerland are all working together to organize our largest event yet: DACHFest!

DACHFest is a two-day DevFest conference focused on making a difference. Meet technology experts, discover all the different ways in which emerging technology is transforming lives, find out how to make your apps and websites friendly towards everyone, learn the secrets of building and nurturing a diverse community — let our speakers surprise and inspire you! And don't forget to make new friends: there will be plenty of opportunities to meet people passionate about your favorite things. ❤️

Join us in Munich on November 10–11 for two days full of talks, workshops, showcases, networking, and fun!

DACHFest is a paid event, but diversity scholarships are available for people who belong to underrepresented groups in tech or cannot afford a ticket.

Website: https://dachfest.com
Twitter: https://twitter.com/dachfest

events.name: Women Techmakers Vienna Conference 2019 #IWD #WTMVIE19

venue.name: Domed hall of the Vienna University of Technology

events.description:
PLEASE register ONLY on: https://wtm-vienna-2019.eventbrite.com/
Schedule: https://www.womentechmakers.at/
People of all genders are welcome to attend our event.
As always, we try to focus on the accomplishments of technologists that also happen to be women, rather than just focusing on the story of doing something as a woman. This helps the focus be more of the work rather than our gender.
We aim to keep things positive when selecting panels, talks, keynotes, etc. We know that we need more women in tech and there are issues we face in the industry, but one of the most powerful things we can do to counter act that is to show the women doing great things and what we are achieving.
